Project Planning – Secure File Drop Web App
Phase 1 – Research & Environment Setup (Week 1)

Tasks:

Install Python (if not already installed).

Install Streamlit (pip install streamlit) and Cryptography library (pip install cryptography).

Test Streamlit with a “Hello World” app to confirm environment works.

Research AES encryption standards and file upload limits.

Draft a basic design layout (upload button, download button, message box).

Deliverable: A running “Hello World” web app in Streamlit + documented workflow for file handling.

Phase 2 – Encryption & File Handling (Weeks 2–3)

Tasks:

Write a Python function to encrypt files using AES-256.

Write a function to decrypt files.

Implement temporary storage of encrypted files.

Test with sample files (PDF, DOCX, TXT).

Make sure decryption returns original file intact.

Deliverable: Python scripts that can successfully encrypt and decrypt files on command.

Phase 3 – One-Time Link System (Week 4)

Tasks:

Generate unique download links (random strings or UUIDs).

Add logic to make each link usable only once.

Implement file auto-delete after download or after set expiry time (e.g., 24 hours).

Test links in multiple browsers and devices.

Deliverable: Fully functional one-time link generator that ensures files cannot be reused or redownloaded.

Phase 4 – User Interface Development (Weeks 5–6)

Tasks:

Build a Streamlit web interface with:

File upload button.

Download link generator.

Status messages (e.g., “File uploaded & encrypted”, “Download ready”).

Ensure interface is simple and clean for non-technical users.

Optional: Add a password option for download links.

Deliverable: A working Streamlit web interface for uploading and downloading files securely.

Phase 5 – Testing & Security Review (Week 7)

Tasks:

Test uploads and downloads with different file types.

Test link expiry and single-use restrictions.

Perform basic security checks:

Ensure no plaintext storage.

Ensure expired links fail.

Collect feedback from a small group of users (friends/classmates).

Deliverable: Bug-free, secure prototype validated against test cases.

Phase 6 – Deployment & Documentation (Week 8)

Tasks:

Push code to GitHub (for version control).

Deploy web app on Streamlit Cloud (free hosting).

Prepare project documentation:

User manual (how to use the system).

Technical report (methods, encryption details, and limitations).

Demo app for department/staff/students.

Deliverable: Online working system + final project documentation and presentation.
